  "prompt": "Does Reliance JIO 4G require internet to make voice calls?",
  "response": "Yes, Reliance JIO 4G uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology to facilitate voice calls. This means that voice calls are transmitted over the 4G data network rather than traditional 2G or 3G circuits. Here\u2019s what that entails:\n\n1. **Integrated Data and Voice**: With VoLTE, both your voice calls and internet data run simultaneously on the same 4G network. This allows for clearer and faster call connections compared to older technologies.\n\n2. **No Need for Separate Networks**: You don\u2019t need to rely on a separate 2G or 3G network for voice calls. Everything operates within the 4G infrastructure provided by JIO.\n\n3. **Requirements**:\n   - **Compatible Device**: Ensure that your smartphone supports VoLTE. Most modern smartphones are compatible, but it\u2019s always good to check your device specifications.\n   - **Active Data Connection**: While making a voice call via VoLTE does use the data network, it\u2019s seamlessly integrated into your call experience. You don\u2019t need to have an active data plan separate from your regular JIO service to make and receive calls.\n\n4. **Benefits**:\n   - **Better Call Quality**: Enhanced voice clarity and reduced call drops.\n   - **Simultaneous Usage**: You can use data-intensive applications (like browsing the web or streaming) while on a call without interrupting the call.\n\nIn summary, while Reliance JIO\u2019s 4G network does use the data connection to handle voice calls through VoLTE, this is built into the standard service. You don\u2019t need to manage a separate internet connection for making voice calls; it\u2019s all part of the 4G service provided by JIO.\n\nIf you\u2019re experiencing issues with making voice calls on JIO\u2019s 4G network, consider the following troubleshooting steps:\n\n- **Enable VoLTE**: Go to your phone\u2019s network settings and ensure that VoLTE is enabled.\n- **Update Your Device**: Make sure your smartphone\u2019s software is up to date.\n- **Check Coverage**: Ensure you\u2019re in an area with strong JIO 4G coverage.\n- **Contact JIO Support**: If problems persist, reaching out to JIO customer service may help resolve network-specific issues.",
